<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREF.5B.5BInternational_Auxiliary_Language_Association.5D.5D1971"><a href="/wiki/International_Auxiliary_Language_Association" title="International Auxiliary Language Association">International Auxiliary Language Association</a> (1971) [1951]. <a href="/wiki/Alexander_Gode" title="Alexander Gode">Alexander Gode</a> (ed.). ed. <i><a href="http://www.bowks.net/worldlang/aux/b_IED.html" class="external text" title="http://www.bowks.net/worldlang/aux/b_IED.html" rel="nofollow">Interlingua-English; a dictionary of the international language</a></i>. "Foreword" and "Acknowledgements" by Mary Connell Bray (Second Edition ed.). <a href="/wiki/New_York" title="New York">New York</a>: Frederick Ungar Publishing. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0804401888" class="internal">ISBN 0-8044-0188-8</a>. <a href="/wiki/Online_Computer_Library_Center" title="Online Computer Library Center">OCLC</a> <a href="http://worldcat.org/oclc/162319" class="external text" title="http://worldcat.org/oclc/162319" rel="nofollow">162319</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.bowks.net/worldlang/aux/b_IED.html" class="external free" title="http://www.bowks.net/worldlang/aux/b_IED.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.bowks.net/worldlang/aux/b_IED.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-03-05</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Interlingua-English%3B+a+dictionary+of+the+international+language&amp;rft.aulast=%5B%5BInternational+Auxiliary+Language+Association%5D%5D&amp;rft.au=%5B%5BInternational+Auxiliary+Language+Association%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=1971&amp;rft.edition=Second+Edition&amp;rft.place=%5B%5BNew+York%5D%5D&amp;rft.pub=Frederick+Ungar+Publishing&amp;rft_id=info:oclcnum/162319&amp;rft.isbn=0-8044-0188-8&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bowks.net%2Fworldlang%2Faux%2Fb_IED.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Interlingua"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li>Pei, Mario. <i>One Language for the World and How To Achieve It.</i> Devin-Adair, New York; 1958.</li>
<li>Union Mundial pro Interlingua (UMI). <a href="http://www.interlingua.com/historia/index.html" class="external text" title="http://www.interlingua.com/historia/index.html" rel="nofollow"><i>Interlingua 2001: communication sin frontieras durante 50 annos</i></a> (in Interlingua). Accessed <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2006-08-17"><a href="/wiki/August_17" title="August 17">17 August</a> <a href="/wiki/2006" title="2006">2006</a></span>.</li>
</ul>
